---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ImageLightbox from '../components/ImageLightbox.astro';
import createUserSwagger from '../screenshots/Create_User_Swagger.PNG';
import loginUserSwagger from '../screenshots/Login_User_Swagger.PNG';
---

<Layout title="User Authentication & JWT Security - Abaki">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-12 md:py-20">
        <a href="/abaki-overview" class="mb-8 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">
            <span class="mr-2">&larr;</span>
            Back to Abaki Overview
        </a>

        <article>
            <header class="mb-12">
                <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl text-white">
                    User Authentication & JWT Security
                </h1>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">
                    Building a secure authentication system with JWT tokens and BCrypt password hashing
                </p>
            </header>

            <section class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Overview</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        The authentication system is the foundation of Abaki's security. It handles user registration, 
                        login, password hashing, and JWT token generation. Every protected API endpoint requires a valid 
                        JWT token in the Authorization header, which is verified using standard claims-based authorization.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
                        This implementation avoids ASP.NET Core Identity, instead building a lightweight, custom solution 
                        tailored to Abaki's needs. Passwords are never stored in plain text and tokens expire after a 
                        configured duration.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Learning Journey</h2>
                    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">🔍 Challenge 1: Choosing Authentication Strategy</h3>
                            <p>
                                Initially considered using ASP.NET Core Identity, but realized it was overkill for Abaki's 
                                needs. Decision: Build a lightweight custom solution with JWT instead. This taught me when 
                                to use framework features vs. custom implementations.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">🔐 Challenge 2: Password Security</h3>
                            <p>
                                Learned the importance of using BCrypt instead of simple hashing. BCrypt automatically handles 
                                salt generation and uses adaptive time costs to make brute-force attacks impractical. Implementing 
                                this properly was crucial.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">🎟️ Challenge 3: JWT Token Generation</h3>
                            <p>
                                Understanding JWT structure (header, payload, signature) and implementing claim-based authorization. 
                                The biggest lesson: tokens need proper expiration handling and validation on every request.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">✅ Key Learning</h3>
                            <p>
                                Security isn't something to add later—it must be baked into the design from the start. Proper 
                                authentication patterns protect both users and the system itself.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Authentication Screenshots</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                        The authentication flow is visible end-to-end through Swagger-facing examples for both user creation and login.
                    </p>
                    <ImageLightbox
                        images={[
                            {
                                src: createUserSwagger,
                                alt: 'Swagger UI for creating a new Abaki user',
                                caption: 'Swagger example for the user registration endpoint.'
                            },
                            {
                                src: loginUserSwagger,
                                alt: 'Swagger UI for logging in to Abaki',
                                caption: 'Swagger example for the login endpoint and returned JWT response.'
                            }
                        ]}
                    />
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Key Code Implementation</h2>
                    
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">Password Hashing on Registration</h3>
                        <div class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden">
                            <pre class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// UserService.cs
public async Task AddAsync(User user)
{
    _logger.LogInformation("Adding new user: {Username}", user?.Name);
    
    await ValidateAsync(user, isNew: true);
    
    // Hash password BEFORE saving to database
    user.Password = BCrypt.Net.BCrypt.HashPassword(user.Password);
    
    _db.Users.Add(user);
    await _db.SaveChangesAsync();
    
    _logger.LogInformation("Successfully added new user '{Username}'", user.Name);
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            BCrypt generates a random salt and uses adaptive time costs. The resulting hash includes the salt, 
                            so we don't need to store it separately.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">Login & JWT Token Generation</h3>
                        <div class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden">
                            <pre class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// UserController.cs
[HttpPost("login")]
public async Task<IActionResult> Login([FromBody] LoginRequest request)
{
    _logger.LogInformation("[Login] Attempt for user {User}", request?.Name);
    
    if (request == null || string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(request.Name))
        return BadRequest(new { error = "Invalid request." });

    // Check password using BCrypt.Verify (timing-safe comparison)
    var valid = await _userService.CheckPasswordAsync(
        request.Name, 
        request.Password
    );
    if (!valid) 
        return Unauthorized(new { message = "Invalid credentials." });

    var apiUser = await _userService.GetByNameAsync(request.Name);
    if (apiUser == null) 
        return StatusCode(500, new { error = "Internal error." });

    // Generate JWT token with claims
    var token = GenerateJwtToken(apiUser);

    return Ok(new
    {
        token,
        user = new UserDto { Id = apiUser.Id, Name = apiUser.Name }
    });
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Password verification uses BCrypt.Verify(), which is a timing-safe comparison that prevents 
                            timing attacks.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">JWT Token Generation with Claims</h3>
                        <div class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden">
                            <pre class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// UserController.cs
private string GenerateJwtToken(User user)
{
    var securityKey = new SymmetricSecurityKey(
        Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(_config["Jwt:SecretKey"]!)
    );
    var credentials = new SigningCredentials(securityKey, SecurityAlgorithms.HmacSha256);

    // Claims are the token payload
    var claims = new[]
    {
        new Claim(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier, user.Id.ToString()),
        new Claim(ClaimTypes.Name, user.Name),
        new Claim("sub", user.Id.ToString())
    };

    var token = new JwtSecurityToken(
        issuer: _config["Jwt:Issuer"],
        audience: _config["Jwt:Audience"],
        claims: claims,
        expires: DateTime.UtcNow.AddHours(24), // Token expires in 24 hours
        signingCredentials: credentials
    );

    return new JwtSecurityTokenHandler().WriteToken(token);
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Claims encode user information into the token. The token is signed with a secret key that only 
                            the server knows, making it tamper-proof.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Technology Stack</h2>
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                        {['C#', 'JWT', 'BCrypt.Net-Next', 'ASP.NET Core', 'Entity Framework Core', 'SigningCredentials'].map((tech) => (
                            <span class="rounded-full border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-300">
                                {tech}
                            </span>
                        ))}
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Results & Impact</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        This authentication system provides:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mt-3">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Secure Credentials:</strong> Passwords are hashed with BCrypt, making them safe even if the database is compromised</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Stateless Auth:</strong> JWT tokens are self-contained, no session storage needed on server</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Fine-grained Authorization:</strong> Claims allow role-based and permission-based access control</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Token Expiration:</strong> Tokens expire after 24 hours, limiting the window for compromised tokens</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Audit Logging:</strong> All login attempts and user creation are logged for security auditing</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>
